SASS has many more functions than LESS
I think I'm gonna have to do some tests with these two. I'm leaning more towards LESS at the moment though.
SASS only has a server side compiler, but it does compile automatically. LESS has also has client side JS compiler and minification.
LESS allows name space definitions - for better code organisation. The escaping function seems clumsy though.
I prefer the syntax of LESS, mixin syntax is more intuitive. Variables in SASS are more useful.
It's hard to choose between SASS and LESS...
